Activity event typing:
  Plan asked to "Add it to the existing worker/src/activity/events.ts typing
  (or wherever connection_expired already lives)". There is no such typed
  events module in the repo — the existing connection_expired event is
  emitted ad-hoc via ctx.publish({ type: 'connection_expired', payload: { ... } })
  from worker/src/tools/composio_call.ts. The new browser_login_required
  and browser_session_expired events follow the same pattern (ctx.publish
  with kind in payload) so SSE consumers parse them identically.

Goto_url integration sequence (per E.3 do-block):
  1. If ctx.browserSites set: loadStorageStateForUrl(url) — savedState or null.
     If savedState: emit browser_session_storage_state_not_supported (E.2 wire).
  2. harnessGotoUrl(session, url) — actual navigation.
  3. If ctx.browserSites set: readPageTextSafely (innerText, 64 KB cap, null on error)
     → detectSignInWall(pageText, url):
       - gated + no saved state    → emit browser_login_required + return
                                     {ok:false, error:{code:'browser_login_required'}}
       - gated +    saved state    → emit browser_session_expired
       - !gated +   saved state    → markBrowserSiteVerified
       - !gated + no saved state   → no-op
  4. Return the raw navigation result.

Notes:
  - The pure detector is tested independently of the harness; the goto_url
    integration is covered end-to-end by E.5's live verify (real LinkedIn
    profile read after connect). No mock harness test for goto_url was
    added — the existing goto_url usage is exercised by other suites and
    a unit test for the wiring would mock 4 modules (harness, loader,
    detector, ctx.publish) which is mostly mock-of-mock.
  - markBrowserSiteVerified call-site moved from E.2's deferred status to
    fully wired here (E.3) — it now fires on every navigation where the
    detector returns negative AND a saved state exists for the host.
  - The form-marker branch is an addition beyond the literal spec phrasing
    ("common login form selectors detected via the harness's existing DOM
    probe"); the simpler regex on the already-fetched text blob is cheaper
    and catches the same cases without an extra CDP round-trip.
